FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1776197153
OL,3,CHow Trump's Strait of Hormuz blockade
OL,4,Cis pulling China off the sidelines
OL,6,FSpeaking at a daily press briefing in
OL,7,FBeijing Guo Jiakun said: "Such actions
OL,8,Fwill only intensify contradictions,
OL,9,Fexacerbate tensions, undermine the
OL,10,Falready fragile ceasefire, and further
OL,11,Fjeopardize the security of navigation
OL,12,Fthrough the strait."
OL,14,FUp until now Chinese vessels, have
OL,15,Fbeen among the few managing to make
OL,16,Ftheir way through the strait, either
OL,17,Fwith the permission of Iran, or having
OL,18,Freportedly paid a million-dollar toll.
OL,26,@oD@ZOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1776197153
OL,3,CHow Trump's Strait of Hormuz blockade
OL,4,Cis pulling China off the sidelines
OL,6,FIran has insisted that the strait is
OL,7,Fopen to allies, those with which it
OL,8,Fhas good relations and can negotiate
OL,9,Fdirectly.
OL,11,FChina, Malaysia, India and Pakistan
OL,12,Fare among the countries who have
OL,13,Fmanaged to get tankers through, but
OL,14,Fonly a handful have safely transited
OL,15,Fthe strait in the last month.
OL,17,FChina is by far the biggest trading
OL,18,Fpartner of not just Iran, but most of
OL,19,Fthe Gulf region.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1776197153
OL,3,CHow Trump's Strait of Hormuz blockade
OL,4,Cis pulling China off the sidelines
OL,6,FWhile, so far, its large economy and
OL,7,Fvaried energy infrastructure has been
OL,8,Fsomewhat insulated from the crisis
OL,9,Fcreated by the war, that won't be the
OL,10,Fcase if the conflict continues and the
OL,11,FStrait of Hormuz becomes a military
OL,12,Fbattleground.
OL,14,FThe angry response from the Chinese
OL,15,FForeign Ministry is also aimed at the
OL,16,FUS president's comments that China
OL,17,Fwould be hit with 50% tariffs if it's
OL,18,Ffound to be supplying Iran with
OL,19,Fweapons.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
